text.section:
A carrier that markets long-term care insurance in the State shall:
establish marketing procedures to ensure that any comparison of policies by insurance producers of the carrier will be fair and accurate;
establish marketing procedures to prevent the sale or issuance of excessive insurance;
establish procedures for verifying compliance with this subsection;
provide, to the extent possible, information on any senior citizen counseling program;
display prominently on the first page of the outline of coverage and the policy the following:
make every reasonable effort to identify whether a prospective applicant:
already has long-term care insurance and, if so, the types and amounts of the long-term care insurance;
had long-term care insurance in force during the last 12 months;
is covered under the medical assistance program; or
intends to replace any existing medical or health insurance coverage with long-term care insurance.
